# WordPress Docker Development Environment

This is a WordPress development environment using Docker Compose. Key project structure:

- [docker-compose.yml](mdc:docker-compose.yml) - Docker configuration for WordPress and MySQL services
- [wordpress/](mdc:wordpress/) - Local WordPress installation directory (mounted to container)
  - [wordpress/wp-config.php](mdc:wordpress/wp-config.php) - Main WordPress configuration
  - [wordpress/wp-content/themes/](mdc:wordpress/wp-content/themes/) - WordPress themes
  - [wordpress/wp-content/plugins/](mdc:wordpress/wp-content/plugins/) - WordPress plugins

## Environment Details
- WordPress runs on `http://localhost:8000`
- Database: `wordpress` (user: `root`, password: `root`, host: `db`)
- All changes to `wordpress/` directory are immediately reflected in the container

## Docker Commands
- Start: `docker-compose up -d`
- Stop: `docker-compose down`  
- Logs: `docker-compose logs -f wordpress`
- Rebuild: `docker-compose down && docker-compose up -d --build`